BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Chapter 1: Understanding Keto) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 674.2 Td (What Is Nutritional Ketosis?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 656.2 Td (Ketosis is a metabolic state where your body primarily uses fat \(converted to ketones\) for) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 642.2 Td (energy instead of glucose from carbohydrates. This happens when carb intake is low enough) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 628.2 Td (\(typically under 20-50g net carbs daily\).) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 600.4 Td (Standard Keto Macros) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 584.4 Td (- Fat: 70-75% of calories) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 570.4 Td (- Protein: 20-25% of calories) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 556.4 Td (- Net Carbs: 5-10% of calories \(20-50g\)) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 526.6 Td (Benefits of Keto) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 508.6 Td (- Weight loss \(especially body fat\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 494.6 Td (- Stable energy \(no crashes\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 480.6 Td (- Reduced hunger and cravings) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 466.6 Td (- Mental clarity and focus) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 452.6 Td (- Improved blood sugar and insulin) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 438.6 Td (- Reduced inflammation) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 424.6 Td (- Better triglycerides and HDL cholesterol) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 394.8 Td (The Keto Flu \(and How to Avoid It\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 376.8 Td (During the transition period \(days 2-7\), you may experience:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 362.8 Td (- Fatigue and brain fog) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 348.8 Td (- Headaches) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 334.8 Td (- Irritability) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 320.8 Td (- Muscle cramps) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 306.8 Td (- Nausea) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 279.0 Td (Prevention:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 263.0 Td (- Electrolytes: Sodium \(5-7g\), Potassium \(3-4g\), Magnesium \(300-400mg\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 249.0 Td (- Drink plenty of water \(dehydration is common\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 235.0 Td (- Don't restrict calories initially - eat until full) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 221.0 Td (- Rest more during adaptation \(1-2 weeks\)) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
